cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper proposes a modification to the standard convolutional block of CNN for image classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the encoding of information and invariance properties in deep CNN architectures, which suggests a possible fit with sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed modification involves the activation function step before pooling, which could also relate to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
